This page is a supplementary teaching scaffold for diagnostics and identity.

## Core concept

A diagnostic is structured compiler data that can be rendered differently without changing its semantic identity.

## Beanstalk boundary

- `CompilerDiagnostic` represents user-facing failures.
- `CompilerError` represents internal or infrastructure failures.
- Every user-facing diagnostic has a stable code and descriptor.
- Payloads carry facts, identities and source locations rather than pre-rendered prose.
- One compilation boundary owns the render context needed by later output.
- Parallel deltas merge in deterministic order before rendering.

Process-local string IDs and absolute paths are not persistent semantic identity.

## Rewrite focus

Explain stable diagnostic contracts, source spans, symbol interning, deferred rendering and deterministic remapping.

Canonical details live in `docs/compiler-design-overview.md`.
